    • Method Detail

      • getGeoLocation

        GeoLocationDetails getGeoLocation(String remoteIP,
                                List<String> resolvedIPs,
                                String inferredCountry)
        Return a GeoLocationDetails object for the provided parameters.
        Parameters:
        remoteIP - The direct remote address of the client
        resolvedIPs - The customer and proxy addresses (if any) used to connect to the server. the customer's address is always the first
        inferredCountry - the country inferred from the InferredCountryResolver implementation, can be null
